reviewText:
one of Coonabarabran's finest exports.
a fun film with no 'lowlights'.

buy and 'renjoy'

Just an old Australian film with Bruce Spence, not really all that great or anything.  But it is special in a simple way, can't say exactly.  If I had to dump films from my collection, I would let a ton of the American ones go first.

A comedy targeting poor tastes of viewers following an Aussie correspondent having travelled forty years ago to a sleepy country town, writing of a local life.

Mix of male and female nudity, transversi and utilizing the sexual urges just to make a film itself.
Adapted from a stage play. Makes Picnic at Hanging Rock look like an Oscar contender.  Some nudity and drunkenness fail to distract from a poor story line
